        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1118264153" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6147937551909113944">I love Ruin. He is ever changing. This book continues right where the last left off. And this crazy journey, just continues to get even crazier. More characters are introduced, that are even more freighting than Ruin. Yes, Ruin does have his moments of: &quot;What the hell was that!&quot; But if there is one thing we can count on, its his ever growing fascination for Isadore. Their relationship is an confusing one. They both need something from each other, yet both hold deep secrets that hold them back fr</span>
  <span id="freeText6147937551909113944" style="display:none">I love Ruin. He is ever changing. This book continues right where the last left off. And this crazy journey, just continues to get even crazier. More characters are introduced, that are even more freighting than Ruin. Yes, Ruin does have his moments of: "What the hell was that!" But if there is one thing we can count on, its his ever growing fascination for Isadore. Their relationship is an confusing one. They both need something from each other, yet both hold deep secrets that hold them back from moving forward. But as each mission continues to get more complicated, Ruin and Isadore grow closer together. . But Ruin is in need of Isadore, for He is Hers, but she is holding herself back from him. There are events she is not ready to let go of, embarrassed and afraid that if Ruin were to find out, she would lose him. But Walls are meant to be torn down!<br /><br /><b>
  <i>"Ruin stroked her cheek, sensing that what he was about to attempt would change things in a way he wasn’t sure would be good or bad for her. Or him, even. Ruin knew she was nervous, he could feel it pushing at his power. He finally allowed his power to push back in a soft wave of something conducive for what he needed to do. Which was distract her while he got around that wall. “Close your eyes,” Ruin said, doing the same, using his supernatural sensors to guide him."</i>
</b><br /><br />Just when things started to get exciting and bizarre, and you think all is right, a bomb is thrown! Completely throwing you off your guessing game. But I can't wait to find out what is next to come!<br /></span>
